Package tree.node

Class GenericTreeNode<NODETYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tree.node.GenericTreeNode<NODETYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    NODETYPE - The typeparameter defines the type of the value associated with the GenericTreeNode. It is replaced with the concrete type during instantiation.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, ITreeNode<NODETYPE>, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<NODETYPE>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CategoryTreeNode, CopyableTreeNode, ProductTreeNode
    public class GenericTreeNode<NODETYPE>
extends Object
implements ITreeNode<NODETYPE>
    This class represents an entry in an ITree and implements the ITreeNode interface. Each entry has a label and a value and is either a leaf (if it does not have child ITreeNodes) or not. The value of the GenericTreeNode is generic and given via the TREETYPE typeparameter. The type of the child ITreeNodes is the same as the type of the current GenericTreeNode. So, in essence, children of the GenericTreeNode can only consist of ITreeNodes of the same type. The concrete type is set during instantiation.
    Author:
    OOP

      • generateConsoleView

        public String generateConsoleView​(String spacer,
                                  String preamble)
        Generates a String representation of the ITreeNode containing itself and all its children. Each ITreeNode in the output is a single entry in a separate line.

        The Object.toString() method is used to generate the String representation of ITreeNodes. Each entry is indented by the passed preamble. The type of the entry, whether it is a leaf or not, is indicated by a leading character. If the current entry is a leaf the leading character is-, otherwise it is +. The entry is completed with a line break.

        Output current entry: [PREAMBLE][TYPE][TOSTRING]
        Example:
        Preamble: ___
        value of entry: "Coffee"
        type: leaf
        Output: ___-GenericTreeNode:Coffee

        If the ITreeNode has children, then the ITreeNode.generateConsoleView(String, String) is invoked on them as well. All child ITreeNodes are indented by the concatenation of the preamble and the spacer and the result of the invocations are conjoined with the current String representation.

        Example:
        Preamble: ___
        Spacer: _
        value of entry: "Coffee"
        type: has children
        Output:
        ___+GenericTreeNode:Coffee
        ____+CoffeeChild1
        ____+CoffeeChild2
        ____+CoffeeChild3

        The Strings "CoffeeChild1"... have to be replaced by the result of the Object.toString() method of the corresponding child ITreeNode.

        The ITreeNode.generateConsoleView(String, String) method is invoked recursively on all children.

        Specified by:
        generateConsoleView in interface ITreeNode<NODETYPE>
        Parameters:
        spacer - The String that should be used to separate ITreeNodes in the output.
        preamble - specifies the leading characters for the ITreeNode
        Returns:
        the generated String output of the ITreeNode

      • deepCopy

        public GenericTreeNode<NODETYPE> deepCopy()
        Creates a copy of the GenericTreeNode and all its attributes and returns it. All attributes that implement the IDeepCopy interface have to be copied via the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method as well. This means that also all direct child ITreeNodes which implement the IDeepCopy interface have to be copied via the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method.

        Redefined here to limit the return type of the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method to ITreeNode.

        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 

         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.

      • searchByFilter

        public Collection<ITreeNode<NODETYPE>> searchByFilter​(ISearchFilter filter,
                                                      Object compareObject)
        Searches for a ITreeNode using an ISearchFilter. Comparison between the ITreeNode and the passed object is done via the ISearchFilter.searchFilterFunction(Object, Object) method. A hit will evaluated in the following steps:
        • Use the ITreeNode with the ISearchFilter.searchFilterFunction(Object, Object) method to check if it matches the compare object.
        • Use the value of the ITreeNode with the ISearchFilter.searchFilterFunction(Object, Object) method to check if it matches the compare object.
        • Recursively find all ITreeNodes matching the compare object in the sub-tree of the ITreeNode.
        If a ITreeNode is a hit it is only added once to the resulting Collection.
        Specified by:
        searchByFilter in interface ISearchableByFilter<NODETYPE>
        Parameters:
        filter - the ISearchFilter used to check if the ITreeNode matches
        compareObject - the object that is used to compare against
        Returns:
        a Collection of ITreeNodes found by the filter function
